        <!-- Architecture -->
        <div class="project-section alt-bg">
            <h3>Architecture Explanation</h3>
            <p>The Cognito architecture implements multi-layer security:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Cloud9 Instance</strong> – Hosts the Node.js Birds application server.</li>
                <li><strong>S3 Bucket</strong> – Serves static website content with CloudFront distribution.</li>
                <li><strong>CloudFront</strong> – CDN for fast content delivery and HTTPS.</li>
                <li><strong>Cognito User Pool</strong> – Manages user authentication and access tokens.</li>
                <li><strong>Cognito Managed UI</strong> – Handles sign-up, sign-in, and token management.</li>
                <li><strong>Cognito Identity Pool</strong> – Exchanges tokens for temporary AWS credentials.</li>
                <li><strong>IAM Roles</strong> – Define permissions for DynamoDB access.</li>
                <li><strong>DynamoDB Table</strong> – Stores bird sightings data.</li>
                <li><strong>Local Storage</strong> – Browser stores access tokens (3,600 second expiration).</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

