        <!-- Best Practices -->
        <div class="project-section">
            <h3>Notes & Best Practices</h3>
            <p>
                Cognito provides enterprise-grade authentication and authorization:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>Use <strong>User Pools</strong> for user authentication and management.</li>
                <li>Use <strong>Identity Pools</strong> for authorization to AWS services.</li>
                <li>Store <strong>tokens securely</strong> in browser local storage or cookies.</li>
                <li>Implement <strong>token refresh</strong> before expiration (default 3,600 seconds).</li>
                <li>Use <strong>MFA (Multi-Factor Authentication)</strong> for enhanced security.</li>
                <li>Configure <strong>password policies</strong> and complexity requirements.</li>
                <li>Enable <strong>CloudTrail logging</strong> for audit trails.</li>
                <li>Use <strong>least-privilege IAM roles</strong> for service access.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

